out/test/**

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-platform native binaries
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# At publish time the release workflow places `ktav-lsp[.exe]` under
#   bin/<platform>-<arch>/   (e.g. bin/win32-x64/ktav-lsp.exe)
# and packages a per-target VSIX via:
#   vsce package --target <platform>-<arch>
# Each per-target VSIX should ship ONLY the matching subdirectory of bin/,
# not all of them — otherwise every platform's VSIX bundles every binary.
#
# The actual filtering is done by the workflow (a `--target`-aware
# generator overrides this file); for local `vsce package` runs we exclude
# bin/ wholesale by default so a stray `bin/` folder never sneaks into a
# universal VSIX.
bin/**
